<section id="sect-00005">
<title>Adverse Effects and Contraindications</title>
<para id="para-00008">Common adverse effects include tremors, nervousness, headache, and tachycardia. Cold symptoms, migraine, chest pain, bronchitis, and nausea have also been reported. Clients with severe cardiac disease should use albuterol only at the direction of their health care provider due to systemic effects on heart rate and blood pressure (DailyMed, <emphasis effect="italics">Albuterol sulfate</emphasis>, 2023).</para>
