<para id="para-00022">Side effects of both drugs can include dry mouth, headache, nervousness or dizziness, blurred vision, constipation, and cough. Clients with hypersensitivity, narrow-angle glaucoma, and urinary retention should avoid these drugs; they can cause urinary retention and exacerbate symptoms.</para>
