<glossary>
<definition id="def-00001"><term>acetylcholine</term> <meaning>a neurotransmitter that contracts smooth muscles, dilates blood vessels, increases bodily secretions, and reduces heart rate</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00002"><term>adrenergic</term> <meaning>refers to the activation or stimulation of the adrenergic receptors in the sympathetic nervous system</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00003"><term>alpha- and beta-adrenergic agonists</term> <meaning>a class of drugs that stimulate all adrenergic receptors</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00004"><term>anticholinergic drugs</term> <meaning>drugs that inhibit the action of acetylcholine</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00005"><term>beta adrenergic</term> <meaning>activation or stimulation of beta-adrenergic receptors, which are found in various tissues throughout the body</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00006"><term>epinephrine</term> <meaning>a neurotransmitter and hormone, also known as adrenaline; also used as a medication</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00007"><term>norepinephrine</term> <meaning>neurotransmitter and hormone as well as a medication that is used to increase and maintain blood pressure</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00008"><term>sympathomimetic</term> <meaning>producing physiological effects characteristic of the sympathetic nervous system by promoting the stimulation of sympathetic nerves</meaning></definition>
</glossary>
